AB  - Sixteen percent of the European Union's coast is currently eroding despite various measures that are taken to protect shorelines from eroding and flooding. As a result of increasing human activities, the natural process of coastal erosion becomes a problem of growing intensity. Coastal managers rely on types of solutions that have proven to be effective on the short term but disregard the effectiveness on the long term. An approach that stresses the importance of both large and small scales in space and time is often lacking. The Eurosion project aims to provide coastal managers with lessons learned and illustrate those with relevant case studies. The lessons help to establish an approach towards coastal erosion that stresses the importance of long-term effects.
